In Python do:

import zipfile
z = zipfile.ZipInfo(40000*'a')
contents = 10*b'c'
bla = zipfile.ZipFile('long_file_name.zip', mode='w')
bla.writestr(z, contents)
bla.close()



This will create a file with a very long file name:

$ zipinfo bla.zip 
Archive:  bla.zip
Zip file size: 80108 bytes, number of entries: 1
warning:  filename too long--truncating.
?rw-------  2.0 unx       10 b- stor 80-Jan-01 00:00 
1 file, 10 bytes uncompressed, 10 bytes compressed:  0.0%
